editorialNotes.standard: Maintaining healthy habits feels a bit less daunting with a customizable self-care pet at your fingertips. With Finch, your very own companion helps you move through specific goals and guided self-care journeys. Beyond that, you can set goals, reflect, or savor a moment of mindfulness with a library of exercises and soundscapes. With consistency, you’ll uncover more about your virtual pet’s personality—and the app’s robust insights can also help you learn a lot about you and your needs too.

Take a deep breath. That phrase greets you whenever you open Calm. It’s both a call to action and a defining feature of the app’s approach to meditation: You’re going to get through this, and all you need to start is a moment. In the increasingly crowded field of apps for meditation and mindfulness, Calm stands out for its ease of use and attention to (soothing) detail.
editorialNotes.short: Try breathing techniques for quick relaxation.
This all-in-one health tracker makes it easy to count your calories and plan your meals.
Uncover the good and bad about your favorite foods and beauty products.

editorialNotes.standard: It’s hard to make the best even better, but the sequel to Day One lives up to expectations—and then some. The app keeps its interface streamlined but adds a wealth of new valuable features. Your journal entries contain all sorts of information—you can geolocate them, add tons of photos to each entry, and even see your day’s fitness activity. Switch over to the beautiful new photo view when you’re ready to see your world at a glance.
editorialNotes.short: Record journal entries with a tap
Listen to meditative sounds on Apple Watch.
Achieve your fitness and wellness goals.

editorialNotes.standard: Bookend your days with a moment of reflection in stoic., an elegantly designed journaling app made for anyone looking to carve out time for mindfulness. With insightful reflection prompts and breathing exercises, the app is filled with multiple ways to care for your mental health—with inspiration from stoic philosophy at its core.
editorialNotes.short: Meet your daily companion for journaling, meditation and reflection.

editorialNotes.tagline: Focus with music from St. Vincent
editorialNotes.standard: If you’re like us, you need all the help you can get turning rare quiet moments into true meditation. Headspace’s rich, accessible lessons gently explore how to improve mindfulness. Oh, and we love how Headspace’s Apple Watch app lets you hit a literal panic button when extra-stressful situations arise.
editorialNotes.short: Stay relaxed during busy times.

editorialNotes.tagline: Join a live class from home
editorialNotes.standard: With Peloton, working out doesn’t have to happen in a silo. Whether you’re into cycling, running, rowing, or yoga, each on-demand workout class is a community affair with a leaderboard full of others cheering you on as well as themed challenges open to all. Plus, it’s easy to stay motivated thanks to the app’s encouraging coaches, and detailed stats help you stay consistent in maintaining your streak.

Want to break a sweat? Celebrity trainers like actor Gabrielle Union and Queer Eye guru Jonathan Van Ness guide you through challenging routines you can stream on demand, while FitOn’s core fitness team leads live classes nearly every hour of the day.

ios.subtitle: Workout, Ride and Race at Home

editorialNotes.short: Ride and run in the real world and power your avatar across our virtual worlds.

advisories: Infrequent/Mild Alcohol, Tobacco, or Drug Use or References

editorialNotes.standard: As its name suggests, Insight Timer started as a simple timer app for meditating. But it’s evolved into a comprehensive (and award-winning) way to help people reduce anxiety, improve their sleep, and maybe even gain a little insight along the way. It features thousands of guided meditations across a range of styles: Buddhist mindfulness (which channels your inner monk), Kundalini yoga (which focuses on your posture), walking meditation (which is meditation on the move), and many others. Lessons range from just a few minutes to long and luxurious.
editorialNotes.short: Set a timer or relax with guided meditation sessions.

advisories: Infrequent/Mild Alcohol, Tobacco, or Drug Use or References

editorialNotes.standard: Many apps deliver soothing sounds to help you to relax, focus, or sleep. But Endel is one of the few with an algorithm smart enough to customize soundscapes for you in the moment. Sometimes it’s the sounds of the ocean, calming rain, or spherical sounds, all paired with harmonic tone sequences.
editorialNotes.short: Sound adapted to your lifestyle

editorialNotes.standard: An invaluable tool for reaching your weight-loss goals, Lose It! tracks your meals, exercise, and nutrition. Documenting food is effortless with its built-in barcode scanner, searchable list of common grocery items, and database of popular restaurant meals’ nutritional facts. Plus, when you need some extra motivation, the app’s social features make it easy to find inspiration from friends and cheer each other on.
editorialNotes.short: Stay on track and monitor your daily calorie budget.

editorialNotes.standard: There’s nothing like a cute llama to help you stay on top of your hydration goals. All you have to do? Track the liquid you consume with Waterllama. Doing so unlocks a world of characters and tools that help you monitor your overall hydration and create goals that are right for you. Timely reminders and a variety of challenges are also there to help you manage an important part of your well-being with joy.

editorialNotes.short: Bring more happiness and peace into your life with soothing music and meditation.

editorialNotes.standard: Rather than yanking you from your slumber like an alarm clock, this app analyzes your sleep patterns using your device’s microphone, then picks your lightest sleep to rouse you gently.
editorialNotes.short: Keep track of your sleeping habits and wake up feeling rested.

editorialNotes.standard: Making a pledge to get fit is easy, but finding the time to actually move our bodies is hard. Seven’s bite-size workouts don’t require a gym membership or special equipment. Best of all, we can launch these satisfying mini-routines right from Apple Watch—it’s like having a rah-rah personal trainer right on our wrist.
editorialNotes.short: There are no excuses. It’s only seven minutes a day!
Plan your fitness routines and track your progress.

editorialNotes.standard: Pillow is stuffed with ways to improve your sleep. The app tracks your z’s, records your moods, and follows your daily routine to help you establish a consistent sleep pattern, night after night. We love the app’s intersection of sleep and data. Tell Pillow about your daily routine—including your mood, meal times, and amount of caffeine you’ve consumed—and it’ll begin to learn what’s helping and hindering you at night.
editorialNotes.short: Track sleep habits and wake up with a silent alarm
Follow guided workouts by experts.
Customise your yoga practise with the length and level of your class.

editorialNotes.standard: We love that SmartGym creates a full-body or targeted workout based on your skill level and the equipment you have on hand. Or create your own routine by selecting an exercise (plank, overhead press) and setting the number of reps or the duration.
editorialNotes.short: Start today's workout on SmartGym.
